******
[6] New Zealand (Auckland)
Date: Mon 8 Aug 2011
Source: Raion New Zealand News [edited]
http://www.radionz.co.nz/news/national/82002/warning-measles-outbreak-could-spread-nationwide


There are now 104 confirmed cases of the illness, which is 10 more
than a week ago. Richard Hoskins says health agencies have seen 10 to
14 new cases each week for the past 6 weeks. Dr Hoskins says it is not
an epidemic yet, but there is a strong possibility that numbers will
increase dramatically.

He is urging more people to get immunised, especially young people, as
measles is very infectious. Dr Hoskins says measles is usually a mild
illness, but some people experience serious complications.

Waikato also has a spate of measles cases, with 12 confirmed cases, up
by 2 from a week ago.

