******
[7] New Zealand (Auckland)
Date: Mon 8 Aug 2011
Source: Auckland Now [edited]
http://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/5409515/Girls-school-hit-by-measles-outbreak


A measles outbreak has spread to Auckland Girls' Grammar, with the
regional health service confirming that 2 cases recently diagnosed
were from the school. As of this morning [8 Aug 2010], there have been
104 confirmed cases of the disease in the Auckland region, 7 of which
have required hospitalisation. Six further unimmunised people have
been in contact with the disease and are in quarantine.

Auckland Girls' Grammar has been advised to tell all parents about the
highly infectious disease, the Auckland Regional Public Health Service
says. People who have never had measles and are not immunised are
advised to stay away from work, school and public places for 2 weeks
if they come into contact with the disease.

Most cases of measles in the current outbreak have occurred in west
Auckland, although it has spread to the North Shore, Manukau and
central Auckland. One Australian man who visited Waitakere Hospital in
July 2011 is also confirmed to have caught the disease.

The Auckland Regional Public Health Service warns that pregnant women
who catch measles are at risk of miscarriages, still births, and low
birth weights. Pregnant women cannot be immunised against the disease,
but authorities say it is important for family and close contacts to
be vigilant and protect mothers and their unborn children.

[byline: Jessica Tasman-Jones]

